//! Phi3Pipeline — distributed inference forward pass for Microsoft's
//! Phi-3 family on the gnosis Rust mesh. Sibling to `NativeLlamaPipeline`
//! (Qwen2 / LLaMA) and `model_gemma4::Gemma4Pipeline` (Gemma3 / Gemma4).
//!
//! ─── STATUS: SCAFFOLD + FUSED-TENSOR SPLIT LOGIC ─────────────────────
//!
//! Wave-17 attempted a Phi-3-mini conversion against the existing
//! NativeLlamaPipeline path and failed because Phi-3 stores fused
//! Q/K/V and gate/up tensors. The kernel branches expect the LLaMA-class
//! tensor layout (separate `attn_q`, `attn_k`, `attn_v`, `ffn_gate`,
//! `ffn_up`) and there is no existing splitter.
//!
//! Wave-18a (this revision) adds the Q4_K block-aligned splitters
//! (`split_phi3_qkv`, `split_phi3_gate_up`) so the implementing agent
//! can call `mat_vec_q4k(out, x, q_chunk, hidden_dim, hidden_dim)` etc.
//! against the three QKV / two gate-up byte slices without paying for
//! a re-quantize. The kernel surface (`forward_one`,
//! `forward_range_attn_chunk`, `lm_head_only`) still returns Err — see
//! the TODO list below for what's left.
//!
//! ─── TODO LIST FOR THE IMPLEMENTING AGENT ────────────────────────────
//!
//! Phi-3-mini-4k-instruct ground truth (from the Q4_K_M GGUF, 195
//! tensors, 2.39 GiB on disk at /tmp/phi3-dl/):
//!   - hidden_dim = 3072
//!   - num_layers = 32
//!   - num_heads  = 32
//!   - num_kv_heads = 32 (no GQA on phi3-mini; phi3-medium has GQA=10)
//!   - head_dim   = 96
//!   - intermediate_size = 8192 (per gate-or-up half; FUSED tensor
//!                              width is 16384 = 2 × 8192)
//!   - vocab_size = 32064
//!   - rope_theta = 10000.0
//!   - sliding_window = 2048 (4k context, half-window SWA)
//!   - tokenizer  = SentencePiece BPE (Llama-style, NOT Gemma)
//!   - chat_template = `<|user|>\n…<|end|>\n<|assistant|>\n`
//!   - eos_token_id = 32000 (`<|endoftext|>`),
//!     additional stop tokens 32001..32007 (`<|assistant|>`,
//!     `<|placeholder*|>`, `<|end|>`, `<|user|>`)
//!
//! ─── DONE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **Fused QKV split.** `split_phi3_qkv` carves the
//!    Q4_K byte slab into three contiguous output-row chunks. The fused
//!    `blk.N.attn_qkv.weight` is stored as `n=3*hidden_dim` output rows
//!    of `d=hidden_dim` input columns; each row is `(d/256)*144` bytes
//!    contiguous. Splitting along output rows (axis 0 in storage) is
//!    just three byte-range slices — no Q4_K block math, no requant.
//!    For phi3-medium GQA, use `split_phi3_qkv_gqa` instead.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **Fused gate/up split.** `split_phi3_gate_up`
//!    does the same trick for `blk.N.ffn_up.weight`
//!    `[2*intermediate × hidden]`: two contiguous chunks at byte
//!    offsets 0 and `intermediate * (hidden/256) * 144`.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **KV cache wiring.** `Phi3Pipeline` constructors
//!    plumb `kv_base_layer` / `kv_num_layers` exactly like the gemma4
//!    trisplit pattern. Cache uses `KVCache::with_base(...)` from
//!    `kv_cache.rs`; per-worker allocation honours the absolute layer
//!    range so a station owning layer 17 only allocates one slot's
//!    worth of K/V rather than the whole 32-layer slab. Sized at
//!    `phi3_kv_max_seq_len()` (128 on wasm to stay under the 128 MiB
//!    CF Workers cap, 2048 native to match the Phi-3-mini-4k window).
//!    Constructor surface (`new`, `from_parts`, `from_knot`,
//!    `from_knot_with_kv_range`) mirrors `Gemma4Pipeline`.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **RoPE.** `apply_phi3_rope` rotates Q and K with
//!    NeoX-style pairing `(q[i], q[i + head_dim/2])`. Phi-3 uses NeoX
//!    RoPE in both `transformers/modeling_phi3.py` (rotate_half) and
//!    llama.cpp `build_phi3` (`GGML_ROPE_TYPE_NEOX`). `head_dim = 96`
//!    is not a power of 2 but the rotation is dim-pair-local, so it
//!    works fine. `rope_theta = 10000.0`, full-dim rotation (no partial
//!    factor). Native test verifies a hand-computed reference vector.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **SWA mask construction.** `phi3_swa_mask_row`
//!    returns the per-row sliding-window mask (`-inf` outside the
//!    window, `0` inside) for a query at absolute position `pos`
//!    against keys `[0, pos]`. Window size is uniform 2048 across all
//!    32 layers (no global/sliding pattern like Gemma3/4). At
//!    `pos < window` the mask collapses to a plain causal mask. The
//!    actual attention compute (Q @ K^T, softmax, @ V) is left as a
//!    TODO inside `forward_range_attn_chunk` — only the mask helper
//!    is wired here.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **Attention compute (single-head primitive).**
//!    `phi3_attention_one_head` runs the SWA-masked
//!    `score = (q . k_t) / sqrt(head_dim)` → causal+SWA gate
//!    (`phi3_swa_mask_row` semantics inlined for in-place softmax) →
//!    `softmax` → weighted V accumulate path. Operates on a single
//!    head's Q vector + flat per-head K/V slabs `[seq_len × head_dim]`
//!    so it is independent of the cache layout (the integration site
//!    will pass slices into `kv_cache.keys` / `.values`). Reuses
//!    `math::softmax`, `math::dot_product`, `math::accumulate_weighted`.
//!    The full SWA matrix path (prefill) and the multi-head dispatcher
//!    are thin wrappers added when `forward_range_attn_chunk` is wired.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **SwiGLU FFN (f32 + Q4_K test variants).**
//!    `phi3_swiglu_ffn_f32(out, x, gate_w, up_w, down_w, hidden, ffn)`
//!    computes `down @ (silu(gate @ x) * (up @ x))`. The Q4_K wire-up
//!    (`phi3_swiglu_ffn_q4k`) takes the byte-slice halves produced by
//!    `split_phi3_gate_up` plus the unfused `ffn_down` Q4_K bytes and
//!    chains `mat_vec_q4k` calls. Reuses `math::swiglu_inplace`.
//!
//!  [DONE 2026-05-03] **RMSNorm wiring.** `phi3_rmsnorm` is a
//!    convenience wrapper around `math::rms_norm` that bakes the
//!    Phi-3 default epsilon (`1e-5`) so call sites stay tidy. Phi-3
//!    uses standard LLaMA-style RMSNorm (raw weight gamma, NOT the
//!    Gemma3 `(1+w)` shift) on `attn_norm`, `ffn_norm`, and
//!    `output_norm` weights.
//!
//! ─── REMAINING ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//!
//! 1. **Tied lm_head.** Phi-3 ties the lm_head to `token_embd.weight`
//!    (no separate `output.weight`) — confirmed against the GGUF
